#. <section class="sutta" id="sn42.13"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn42.13:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 42"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 42"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.13:0.2"
msgid "1. Gāmaṇivagga"
msgstr "1. Chiefs"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 13. Pāṭaliyasutta → pātali (or manāpo) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn42.13:0.3"
msgid "13. Pāṭaliyasutta"
msgstr "13. With Pāṭaliya"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: uttaraṃ nāma → uttarakaṃ nāma (bj) | uttarannāma (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn42.13:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā koliyesu viharati uttaraṃ nāma koliyānaṃ nigamo."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Koliyans, where they "
"have a town called Uttara."

msgctxt "sn42.13:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho pāṭaliyo gāmaṇi yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho pāṭaliyo "
"gāmaṇi bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Pāṭaliya the chief went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn42.13:1.3"
msgid "“sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante:"
msgstr "“Sir, I have heard this:"

msgctxt "sn42.13:1.4"
msgid "‘samaṇo gotamo māyaṃ jānātī’ti."
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama knows magic.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.341"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.13:2.1"
msgid ""
"Ye te, bhante, evamāhaṃsu: ‘samaṇo gotamo māyaṃ jānātī’ti, kacci te, bhante, "
"bhagavato vuttavādino, na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkhanti, dhammassa "
"cānudhammaṃ byākaronti, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ "
"āgacchati?"
msgstr ""
"Do those who say this repeat what the Buddha has said, and not misrepresent "
"him with an untruth? Is their explanation in line with the teaching? Are "
"there any legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism?"

msgctxt "sn42.13:2.2"
msgid "Anabbhācikkhitukāmā hi mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantan”ti."
msgstr "For we don’t want to misrepresent the Blessed One.”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:2.3"
msgid ""
"“Ye te, gāmaṇi, evamāhaṃsu: ‘samaṇo gotamo māyaṃ jānātī’ti, vuttavādino ceva "
"me, te na ca maṃ abhūtena abbhācikkhanti, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākaronti, "
"na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgacchatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Chief, those who say this repeat what I have said, and don’t misrepresent "
"me with an untruth. Their explanation is in line with the teaching, and "
"there are no legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism.”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:2.4"
msgid "“Saccaṃyeva kira, bho, mayaṃ tesaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ na saddahāma:"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, we didn’t believe that what those ascetics and brahmins said was "
"really true."

msgctxt "sn42.13:2.5"
msgid "‘samaṇo gotamo māyaṃ jānātī’ti, samaṇo khalu bho gotamo māyāvī”ti."
msgstr "But it seems the ascetic Gotama is a magician!”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:2.6"
msgid ""
"“Yo nu kho, gāmaṇi, evaṃ vadeti: ‘ahaṃ māyaṃ jānāmī’ti, so evaṃ vadeti: ‘"
"ahaṃ māyāvī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Chief, does someone who says ‘I know magic’ also say ‘I am a magician’?”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:2.7"
msgid "“Tatheva taṃ bhagavā hoti, tatheva taṃ sugata hotī”ti."
msgstr "“That’s right, Blessed One! That’s right, Holy One!”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:2.8"
msgid ""
"“Tena hi, gāmaṇi, taññevettha paṭipucchissāmi; yathā te khameyya, tathā taṃ "
"byākareyyāsi—"
msgstr ""
"“Well then, brahmin, I’ll ask you about this in return, and you can answer "
"as you like."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.342"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.13:3.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gāmaṇi, "
msgstr "What do you think, chief? "

msgctxt "sn42.13:3.2"
msgid "jānāsi tvaṃ koliyānaṃ lambacūḷake bhaṭe”ti?"
msgstr "Do you know the Koliyan officers with drooping headdresses?”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:3.3"
msgid "“Jānāmahaṃ, bhante, koliyānaṃ lambacūḷake bhaṭe”ti."
msgstr "“I know them, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:3.4"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gāmaṇi, kimatthiyā koliyānaṃ lambacūḷakā bhaṭā”ti?"
msgstr "“And what’s their job?”"

#. VAR: ca vahātuṃ → tāni ca pahātuṃ (s1-3, km) | tāni vahātuṃ (pts1) | tāni ca yātuṃ (katthaci) | tāni cāvahātuṃ (?)
msgctxt "sn42.13:3.5"
msgid ""
"“Ye ca, bhante, koliyānaṃ corā te ca paṭisedhetuṃ, yāni ca koliyānaṃ "
"dūteyyāni tāni ca vahātuṃ, etadatthiyā, bhante, koliyānaṃ lambacūḷakā "
"bhaṭā”ti."
msgstr "“To put a stop to bandits and to deliver messages for the Koliyans.”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:3.6"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gāmaṇi, "
msgstr "“What do you think, chief? "

msgctxt "sn42.13:3.7"
msgid "jānāsi tvaṃ koliyānaṃ lambacūḷake bhaṭe sīlavante vā te dussīle vā”ti?"
msgstr "Are the Koliyan officers with drooping headdresses moral or immoral?”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:3.8"
msgid ""
"“Jānāmahaṃ, bhante, koliyānaṃ lambacūḷake bhaṭe dussīle pāpadhamme; ye ca "
"loke dussīlā pāpadhammā koliyānaṃ lambacūḷakā bhaṭā tesaṃ aññatarā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I know that they’re immoral, of bad character, sir. They are among those in "
"the world who are immoral and of bad character.”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:3.9"
msgid "“Yo nu kho, gāmaṇi, evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "“Would it be right to say that"

msgctxt "sn42.13:3.10"
msgid ""
"‘pāṭaliyo gāmaṇi jānāti koliyānaṃ lambacūḷake bhaṭe dussīle pāpadhamme, "
"pāṭaliyopi gāmaṇi dussīlo pāpadhammo’ti, sammā nu kho so vadamāno vadeyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Pāṭaliya knows the Kolyian officers with drooping headdresses who are "
"immoral, of bad character, so he too must be immoral and of bad character.”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:3.11"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“No, sir."

msgctxt "sn42.13:3.12"
msgid ""
"Aññe, bhante, koliyānaṃ lambacūḷakā bhaṭā, aññohamasmi. Aññathādhammā "
"koliyānaṃ lambacūḷakā bhaṭā, aññathādhammohamasmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"I’m quite different from the Koliyan officers with drooping headdresses, we "
"have quite different characters.”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:3.13"
msgid ""
"“Tvañhi nāma, gāmaṇi, lacchasi: ‘pāṭaliyo gāmaṇi jānāti koliyānaṃ "
"lambacūḷake bhaṭe dussīle pāpadhamme, na ca pāṭaliyo gāmaṇi dussīlo "
"pāpadhammo’ti, kasmā tathāgato na lacchati: ‘tathāgato māyaṃ jānāti, na ca "
"tathāgato māyāvī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"“So if you can know those officers of bad character while you are not of bad "
"character, why can’t the Realized One know magic, without being a magician?"

msgctxt "sn42.13:3.14"
msgid ""
"Māyañcāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, pajānāmi, māyāya ca vipākaṃ, yathāpaṭipanno ca māyāvī "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati "
"tañca pajānāmi."
msgstr ""
"I understand magic and its result. And I understand how magicians practice "
"so that when their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of "
"loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.343"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.13:4.1"
msgid ""
"Pāṇātipātañcāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, pajānāmi, pāṇātipātassa ca vipākaṃ, yathāpaṭipanno "
"ca pāṇātipātī kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ "
"upapajjati tañca pajānāmi."
msgstr ""
"I understand killing living creatures and its result. And I understand how "
"those who kill living creatures practice so that when their body breaks up, "
"after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, "
"hell."

msgctxt "sn42.13:4.2"
msgid ""
"Adinnādānañcāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, pajānāmi, adinnādānassa ca vipākaṃ, yathāpaṭipanno "
"ca adinnādāyī kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ "
"upapajjati tañca pajānāmi."
msgstr "I understand stealing …"

msgctxt "sn42.13:4.3"
msgid ""
"Kāmesumicchācārañcāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, pajānāmi, kāmesumicchācārassa ca vipākaṃ, "
"yathāpaṭipanno ca kāmesumicchācārī kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ "
"duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati tañca pajānāmi."
msgstr "sexual misconduct …"

msgctxt "sn42.13:4.4"
msgid ""
"Musāvādañcāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, pajānāmi, musāvādassa ca vipākaṃ, yathāpaṭipanno ca "
"musāvādī kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ "
"upapajjati tañca pajānāmi."
msgstr "lying …"

msgctxt "sn42.13:4.5"
msgid ""
"Pisuṇavācañcāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, pajānāmi, pisuṇavācāya ca vipākaṃ, yathāpaṭipanno "
"ca pisuṇavāco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ "
"upapajjati tañca pajānāmi."
msgstr "divisive speech …"

msgctxt "sn42.13:4.6"
msgid ""
"Pharusavācañcāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, pajānāmi, pharusavācāya ca vipākaṃ, "
"yathāpaṭipanno ca pharusavāco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ "
"vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati tañca pajānāmi."
msgstr "harsh speech …"

msgctxt "sn42.13:4.7"
msgid ""
"Samphappalāpañcāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, pajānāmi, samphappalāpassa ca vipākaṃ, "
"yathāpaṭipanno ca samphappalāpī kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ "
"vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati tañca pajānāmi."
msgstr "talking nonsense …"

msgctxt "sn42.13:4.8"
msgid ""
"Abhijjhañcāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, pajānāmi, abhijjhāya ca vipākaṃ, yathāpaṭipanno ca "
"abhijjhālu kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ "
"upapajjati tañca pajānāmi."
msgstr "covetousness …"

msgctxt "sn42.13:4.9"
msgid ""
"Byāpādapadosañcāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, pajānāmi, byāpādapadosassa ca vipākaṃ, "
"yathāpaṭipanno ca byāpannacitto kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ "
"vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati tañca pajānāmi."
msgstr "ill will …"

msgctxt "sn42.13:4.10"
msgid ""
"Micchādiṭṭhiñcāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, pajānāmi, micchādiṭṭhiyā ca vipākaṃ, "
"yathāpaṭipanno ca micchādiṭṭhiko kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ "
"vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati tañca pajānāmi."
msgstr ""
"wrong view and its result. And I understand how those who have wrong view "
"practice so that when their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a "
"place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.13:5.1"
msgid "Santi hi, gāmaṇi, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:"

msgctxt "sn42.13:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘yo koci pāṇamatipāteti, sabbo so diṭṭheva dhamme dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedayati."
msgstr ""
"‘Everyone who kills living creatures experiences pain and sadness in the "
"present life."

msgctxt "sn42.13:5.3"
msgid ""
"Yo koci adinnaṃ ādiyati, sabbo so diṭṭheva dhamme dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedayati."
msgstr "Everyone who steals …"

msgctxt "sn42.13:5.4"
msgid ""
"Yo koci kāmesu micchā carati, sabbo so diṭṭheva dhamme dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedayati."
msgstr "commits sexual misconduct …"

msgctxt "sn42.13:5.5"
msgid ""
"Yo koci musā bhaṇati, sabbo so diṭṭheva dhamme dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedayatī’ti."
msgstr "lies experiences pain and sadness in the present life.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.344"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
#. VAR: sunhāto → sunahāto (bj)
msgctxt "sn42.13:6.1"
msgid ""
"Dissati kho pana, gāmaṇi, idhekacco mālī kuṇḍalī sunhāto suvilitto "
"kappitakesamassu itthikāmehi rājā maññe paricārento."
msgstr ""
"But you can see someone, garlanded and adorned, nicely bathed and anointed, "
"hair and beard dressed, taking his pleasure with women as if he were a king."

msgctxt "sn42.13:6.2"
msgid "Tamenaṃ evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "You might ask someone:"

msgctxt "sn42.13:6.3"
msgid ""
"‘ambho, ayaṃ puriso kiṃ akāsi mālī kuṇḍalī sunhāto suvilitto "
"kappitakesamassu itthikāmehi rājā maññe paricāretī’ti?"
msgstr "‘Mister, what did that man do?’"

msgctxt "sn42.13:6.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "And they’d reply:"

msgctxt "sn42.13:6.5"
msgid "‘ambho, ayaṃ puriso rañño paccatthikaṃ pasayha jīvitā voropesi."
msgstr "‘Mister, that man attacked the king’s enemy and killed them."

msgctxt "sn42.13:6.6"
msgid "Tassa rājā attamano abhihāramadāsi."
msgstr "The king was delighted and gave him this reward."

msgctxt "sn42.13:6.7"
msgid ""
"Tenāyaṃ puriso mālī kuṇḍalī sunhāto suvilitto kappitakesamassu, itthikāmehi "
"rājā maññe paricāretī’ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s why he’s garlanded and adorned, nicely bathed and anointed, hair and "
"beard dressed, taking his pleasure with women as if he were a king.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
#. VAR: rathiyāya rathiyaṃ → rathikāya rathikaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn42.13:7.1"
msgid ""
"Dissati kho, gāmaṇi, idhekacco daḷhāya rajjuyā pacchābāhaṃ gāḷhabandhanaṃ "
"bandhitvā khuramuṇḍaṃ karitvā kharassarena paṇavena rathiyāya rathiyaṃ "
"siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ parinetvā, dakkhiṇena dvārena nikkhāmetvā, "
"dakkhiṇato nagarassa sīsaṃ chijjamāno."
msgstr ""
"And you can see someone else, his arms tied tightly behind his back with a "
"strong rope. His head is shaven and he’s marched from street to street and "
"from square to square to the beating of a harsh drum. Then he’s taken out "
"the south gate and there, to the south of the city, they chop off his head."

msgctxt "sn42.13:7.2"
msgid "Tamenaṃ evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "You might ask someone:"

#. VAR: chindatī’ti → chijjatīti (katthaci)
msgctxt "sn42.13:7.3"
msgid ""
"‘ambho, ayaṃ puriso kiṃ akāsi, daḷhāya rajjuyā pacchābāhaṃ gāḷhabandhanaṃ "
"bandhitvā khuramuṇḍaṃ karitvā kharassarena paṇavena rathiyāya rathiyaṃ "
"siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ parinetvā dakkhiṇena dvārena nikkhāmetvā dakkhiṇato "
"nagarassa sīsaṃ chindatī’ti?"
msgstr "‘Mister, what did that man do?’"

msgctxt "sn42.13:7.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "And they’d reply:"

msgctxt "sn42.13:7.5"
msgid "‘ambho, ayaṃ puriso rājaverī itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā jīvitā voropesi, "
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, that man is an enemy of the king who has murdered a man or a woman. "

msgctxt "sn42.13:7.6"
msgid "tena naṃ rājāno gahetvā evarūpaṃ kammakāraṇaṃ kārentī’ti."
msgstr "That’s why the rulers arrested him and inflicted such punishment.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.345"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.13:8.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gāmaṇi, "
msgstr "What do you think, chief? "

msgctxt "sn42.13:8.2"
msgid "api nu te evarūpaṃ diṭṭhaṃ vā sutaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Have you seen or heard of such a thing?”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:8.3"
msgid "“Diṭṭhañca no, bhante, sutañca suyyissati cā”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, we have seen it and heard of it, and we will hear of it again.”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:8.4"
msgid "“Tatra, gāmaṇi, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "“Since this is so, the ascetics and brahmins whose view is that"

msgctxt "sn42.13:8.5"
msgid ""
"‘yo koci pāṇamatipāteti, sabbo so diṭṭheva dhamme dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedayatī’ti, saccaṃ vā te āhaṃsu musā vā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"everyone who kills living creatures experiences pain and sadness in the "
"present life: are they right or wrong?”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:8.6"
msgid "“Musā, bhante”."
msgstr "“They’re wrong, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:8.7"
msgid "“Ye pana te tucchaṃ musā vilapanti, sīlavanto vā te dussīlā vā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But those who speak baseless, false nonsense: are they moral or immoral?”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:8.8"
msgid "“Dussīlā, bhante”."
msgstr "“Immoral, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:8.9"
msgid ""
"“Ye pana te dussīlā pāpadhammā micchāpaṭipannā vā te sammāpaṭipannā vā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“And are those who are immoral, of bad character practicing wrongly or "
"rightly?”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:8.10"
msgid "“Micchāpaṭipannā, bhante”."
msgstr "“They’re practicing wrongly, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:8.11"
msgid "“Ye pana te micchāpaṭipannā micchādiṭṭhikā vā te sammādiṭṭhikā vā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“And do those who are practicing wrongly have wrong view or right view?”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:8.12"
msgid "“Micchādiṭṭhikā, bhante”."
msgstr "“They have wrong view, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:8.13"
msgid "“Ye pana te micchādiṭṭhikā kallaṃ nu tesu pasīditun”ti?"
msgstr "“But is it appropriate to have confidence in those of wrong view?”"

msgctxt "sn42.13:8.14"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.13:9.1"
msgid ""
"“Dissati kho pana, gāmaṇi, idhekacco mālī kuṇḍalī … pe … itthikāmehi rājā "
"maññe paricārento."
msgstr "“You can see someone, garlanded and adorned …"

